# Label & Section-Header Typography (App Default)

Use this for field labels and section headers across workflow/layer pages
(e.g. CLO review, Assessment redesign, and any new pages going forward).
Base typeface is **Inter** (already the app default via `font-sans`).

## Field / sub-labels (default for everything)

Near-black, bold, small uppercase. Use the SAME style in both read and edit
views so a label looks identical whether viewing or editing.

```tsx
<p className="text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider field-label">Official CLO</p>
// edit-view <label> uses the identical classes
```

- size `text-[11px]`, weight `font-bold`, `uppercase`, `tracking-wider`
- color via the `field-label` class (= `text-foreground`, near-black)

## Main section headers (only a few per card)

Reserve the softer blue (`label-accent`) for the few top-level section headers
only — NOT for every field label. Examples: Council Summary, View Full Council
Analysis, AI Suggested Contribution / Refinement, Final Assessment / Final CLO.

```tsx
<h4 className="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide label-accent">AI Suggested Refinement</h4>
```

- `label-accent` is a muted blue (`hsl(221 53% 47%)`; lighter in dark mode) defined
  in `index.css` — softer than `--primary` so small text doesn't strain the eyes.
- Do NOT use raw `text-primary` for small uppercase labels; it's too harsh.

## Body text

Body/value text aligns flush-left with its label and uses:

```tsx
<p className="text-sm leading-relaxed text-foreground/90">...</p>
```

Keep labels and body left-aligned (no extra `pl-*`/`ml-*` indents) and avoid
decorative vertical bars before labels or boxes/backgrounds around collapsibles.
